const coverLetterPrompt = `You are an expert cover letter writer who specializes in helping software engineers land jobs at top tech companies. Write a highly compelling, personalized, one-page cover letter for this specific job application.

CANDIDATE PROFILE:
Name: <YOUR_FULL_NAME>
Location: <YOUR_CITY_STATE>
Contact: <YOUR_EMAIL> | +13128893640 | linkedin.com/in/<YOUR_LINKEDIN_ID> | <YOUR_PORTFOLIO_URL>
Education: MS Computer Science, UIC (GPA 4.0, May 2026) | BS CS Engineering, VIT India (GPA 3.6)

EXPERIENCE DEPTH — use these to go beyond what the resume says:
- RadioFX Co-op (Sept-Dec 2025): Sole engineer on a multi-agent AI pipeline that took a radio station from zero web presence to a fully deployed, production GKE site — automated the entire prompt to code to deployment lifecycle using Gemini 2.5/3 Pro and Vercel v0. Also owned the full CMS architecture end-to-end using NestJS and Cassandra, designed the JWT API contract, and personally shipped the CI/CD pipelines.
- RadioFX Intern (Jun-Aug 2025): Took ownership of migrating all legacy services to GKE — designed the cluster architecture with isolated dev/prod namespaces from scratch, not just followed instructions. Built Cloud Build and GitHub Actions pipelines with zero-downtime deployment guarantees.
- Bajaj Finserv Health SDE (Sept 2023-Jul 2024): Reduced codebase errors by 80% by building automated validation pipelines — this directly unblocked the B2C and Doctor Portal teams from daily firefighting. Designed and shipped CanvasRx entirely — a real-time image annotation tool used by doctors in live consultations, improving the quality of patient care workflows.
- Bajaj Finserv Health Associate SDE (Jul 2022-Sept 2023): Maintained modules that served 98% of all website traffic — high-stakes, high-ownership role with zero tolerance for downtime. The AMP optimization that moved PageSpeed from 65 to 99 was entirely self-initiated, not assigned — identified the problem, proposed the solution, and shipped it.
- Bajaj Finserv Health Intern (Jan-Jun 2022): Fixed 10,818 broken SEO URLs which directly recovered organic search traffic for the business. Established SonarQube from scratch — the team had zero test coverage before this, and this initiative raised it to 55%.

SKILLS: React, TypeScript, Node.js, NestJS, Python, GCP, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, MongoDB, Redis, Cassandra, CI/CD, GitHub Actions, GKE, Helm, NGINX, Gemini API, OpenAI, Jest, TDD, Agile

TARGET JOB:
Role: ${input.title}
Company: ${input.company}
Job Description: ${(input.description || '').substring(0, 800)}

Date: ${new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}

WRITING RULES:
1. Write in plain text only — no markdown, no bullet points, no headers, no bold tags.
2. Sound like a confident, high-ownership engineer — not a generic applicant.
3. Go beyond the resume. Reveal the depth, context, and personal ownership behind the work. Talk about WHY decisions were made and WHAT challenges were solved, not just WHAT was built.
4. Mirror keywords from the job description naturally — weave them in conversationally, do not list them.
5. Every paragraph must make the recruiter think "this person has done exactly this before".
6. Do not fabricate anything — only use experience listed above.
7. Do not use generic openers like "I am writing to express my interest", "I am a passionate engineer", "I would be a great fit". Start strong and specific instead.
8. Each paragraph must flow naturally into the next — this should read like a story of compounding ownership and impact, not a list of jobs.
9. Keep it to exactly 6 paragraphs.
10. The entire letter including header and sign-off MUST be under 400 words. Be concise and punchy — every sentence must earn its place. Cut filler, cut repetition, say more with less.

FORMAT — output exactly this structure with no extra lines or sections:
<YOUR_FULL_NAME> | Chicago, USA | <YOUR_EMAIL> | +13128893640
${new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}

Dear Hiring Team at ${input.company},

[Paragraph 1: 2-3 sentences. Strong specific opening — immediately establish who you are and why this role caught your attention. Reference something specific about the role or company from the job description. No generic openers.]

[Paragraph 2: 3-4 sentences. RadioFX Co-op — go deep on ownership. You were the sole engineer on the AI pipeline. What problem it solved, why GKE and Gemini were the right choices, what it meant to ship a production multi-tenant system end to end. Connect this directly to what the target job needs.]

[Paragraph 3: 2-3 sentences. Technical depth and stack alignment — connect your specific stack to what this job requires. Mention specific architectural decisions you made and why. Do not just list technologies — show you understand how to use them together to solve real problems.]

[Paragraph 4: 2-3 sentences. Bajaj Finserv — emphasize scale, self-initiated ownership, and measurable impact. The 98% traffic, 80% error reduction, PageSpeed 65 to 99, SEO fix — high-stakes decisions with real business consequences, not just assigned tasks.]

